<font color="#FF0000">REPLY TO EDWARD RAMON, AND ALL</font><br>
<tt>Sun Aug 31 14:28:29 US/Eastern 1997
</tt><p>
Oh Edward, you too are guilty (as I sure have been in the past) of the &quot;overreaction syndrome&quot;. By the way, I did not use the word &quot;hopelah&quot; anywhere in my post.  <br><br>
Must have really struck some nerves to get such a powerful post in response.<br><br>
My point is that we used to have Vietnamese contributors, Female contributers, contributers that reflected almost every point of view.  Now the site is dominated by you, Cook, Silent Warrior, and a few others who tend to ack like a SEAL team, or an attack team.  One for all and all for one is good, but it is your group that are the ones I was referring to as those that have seized the site.  That is not to blame you, but to blame those that let you.<br><br>
It is everyone's right to post or to read, to stay or to go. Nothing I said warranted your attack on me.  It was creative, but wrong. I never was a &quot;communist advocate&quot; by the way. Nor am I a coward or a traitor.  Nor did I attack your grandfather or Native Americans. Inflamatory language will not win a battle of wits, Ed. Why don't you look at what it really is that I said that got you so hot?<br><br>
Is the lesson of history that we must fight that damn war over and over, 30 years later?  Seems like it. That means 58,000 Americans died for nothing.  Will we discuss the wonderful feeling of killing human beings, or will we discuss how this one event, this single solitary event that took one or two years out of our lives, and probably made the biggest impact on our generation, if not ruining our generation, has impacted on each of us?<br><br>
The Viet Nam War changed my life, and I was never in the jungle.  It changed yours and you were.  It changed girl friends, wifes, parents, and the very people we were supposed to be saving, the Vietnamese.  Isn't that what the real purpose of this site is, to reflect, to heal, to learn about our mistake so it never repeats?  I think so.<br><br>

<p><code>-- never a commie or traitor be  (doc spatz, patriot &amp; prostestor) </code><p>


